cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC. 

This paper deals with a network model and proposes a distributed algorithm for frequency allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and optimization, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely category. The use of a Markov model and stochastic analysis indicates cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and simulations, which could fall under cs.MA (Machine Learning) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
